{"sequence":20,"timestamp":"2026-04-23T06:20:14.339240480Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-6dd91a3d","body":"finding_summary: The new help text still describes tasks as projects in several visible `about` strings, which violates the bead's vocabulary rule and the acceptance criterion for consistent milestone/bead/task terminology. `ralph-burning task --help` surfaces `Create a task (project) from a bead.`, `Select a task as the active project.`, and `List tasks (bead-backed projects) in the workspace.`, and `ralph-burning milestone --help` surfaces `List tasks (bead-backed projects) for a milestone.` affected_files: src/cli/task.rs:24, src/cli/task.rs:40, src/cli/task.rs:48, src/cli/milestone.rs:129. remediation_hint: Use task-first wording such as `Create a task from a bead.`, `Select a task as the active task.`, `List tasks in the workspace.`, and `List tasks for a milestone.`","dedup_key":"d2b791ccea58005334449d64eed7cfcd5eb9d1c37eb03540d87160e85baf9997","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260423053722","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
