{"sequence":47,"timestamp":"2026-04-24T02:29:13.401874950Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-b09de892","body":"finding_summary: The new `task` help text now claims these commands manage bead-backed tasks only and that `task show` includes milestone/bead lineage, but the implementation still delegates `show`, `select`, and `list` to the generic project store without filtering. `handle_show` accepts any `ProjectId` and only prints lineage when `detail.task_lineage` is present, `handle_select` selects any project ID, and `handle_list` calls `service::list_projects`, which returns every project in the workspace. In mixed workspaces, `ralph-burning task --help`, `task show --help`, and `task list --help` will therefore overpromise task-only behavior. affected_files: src/cli/task.rs:15-16, src/cli/task.rs:29-30, src/cli/task.rs:40-50, src/cli/task.rs:96-130, src/cli/task.rs:154-184, src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs:1391-1409. remediation_hint: Either relax the help text to describe these as task-oriented aliases over project commands and make lineage conditional, or add filtering so the task commands only operate on bead-backed tasks.","dedup_key":"a4354aec80592eb1e3776fb7e3361a36ea85fdb32dbc0cce8d080db1ca1d159a","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260423053722","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
