{"sequence":67,"timestamp":"2026-04-24T03:19:43.334978261Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-7c2e7fc3","body":"Finding: `task show`/`task select` now reject any project without `[task_source]` (`src/cli/task.rs:106-119`, `src/cli/task.rs:155-166`) and `task list` now filters those projects out entirely (`src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs:1399-1422`). That changes the `task` namespace from the alias/wrapper behavior the product still advertises in `src/cli/project.rs:78-85` into a task-source-only view. The regression is user-visible today: a standalone project disappears from `task list`, and `task show <id>` / `task select <id>` fail with `ProjectNotTask` even though `project --help` tells operators to use those commands instead. It also misclassifies legacy bead-backed projects that are still recovered elsewhere via lineage fallback (`src/cli/project.rs:803-829`, `src/cli/project.rs:3881-3946`), because `is_milestone_task()` only checks explicit `task_source`. The rewritten assertions in `tests/cli.rs:19443-19457` and `tests/cli.rs:19628-19684` lock this regression in. Remediation: keep this bead to help-text updates only and revert the new filtering/gating, or preserve the original wrapper semantics plus legacy-lineage detection before tightening task-only behavior.","dedup_key":"dadd447fd0b621a416100a62c7d899dd731d2bf6a7b3b2b187975c29d963f6e0","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260423053722","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
